      width="300"
      height="300"
      loading="lazy"
      class="rounded-lg w-full md:w-auto md:max-w-[280px] shrink-0"
    />
    <div class="flex-1">
      <p>
        Under extremely high centrifugal force inside the rotating bowl, water and sludge are spun outward toward the bowl periphery. Clean diesel moves inward and is continuously discharged through a <strong>light-phase outlet</strong>.
      </p>

      <p>
        The separated water is collected and discharged through a separate passage from the bowl periphery. The accumulated sludge is periodically ejected by the <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge/#self-cleaning-bowl">self-cleaning</a> mechanism built into the bowl.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

